						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in a field to the east of this village.</p>						

						<p>Dēvarāya I, 1414 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1336, Jaya, Ashāḍha ba. 2, Wednesday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1414 A.D., July 4, Wednesday, f.d.t. ·07.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to confer some land as <hi rend="italic">vokkalu</hi> to an individual named Adugātu-uṁgurapaḷḷi (?), by the king and the residents of the village Uḷḷūru (?). It refers to <hi rend="bold">Śaṅkaradēva-oḍeya</hi> as the governor of <hi rend="bold">Bārkūru-rājya.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
